<div class="list-div auto-margin">

  <p class="left">Ever since the James' betrayal, the Infernal Order has searched in vain for their treasure, making it our duty to protect it. With your efforts, we are close to stopping them once again!
</p>
  <p class="left">Although the condition of the journal made many of its pages illegible, our cryptologists have concentrated on the leafs of testimony that have still been preserved. With much diligence, we’ve unearthed a considerable amount of information for you…</p>

<p class="left">After Bill Ryan's arrest, both Captain Green and Charles Eastman waited for confirmation from Frank and Jesse that they had indeed absconded with the troves. When word failed to arrive, Green and Eastman followed the instructions left for them by the two brothers. They each secured the troves of their Temples and moved them to a final resting place, creating a new key to the map. </p>
<p class="left">This new key, authored by Green and Eastman, was amongst the destroyed pages of the journal. But, as luck would have it, Green and Eastman decided to hide the combined troves at the Temple of the Sun, meaning that Jesse’s original key will still work!</p>
<p class="left">The key gives instructions to be followed from the Sam Watkins building to Jesse’s home in Edgefield, and from there, to the Temple of the Sun. Thanks to your brilliance, we are able to take up the hunt from Jesse's house! </p>
